tafsir[2]{c,v,t}:
  9,119,"Whenever a man adopts an arrogant stance, it is on the basis of some backing. But the things on which his arrogance depends for support have no value in this universe. Nothing has any power here, for the sole possessor of power is God. All are dependent on Him and He is not dependent on anyone. So, on the Day of Judgement, only those who had sought out the real support, who had made the true faith the religion of their lives, will be successful."
  9,122,"‘preaching’, while that of the addressee ends only on his ‘fulfilling his religious obligations’."